T1  - Competitive Search Equilibrium
AU  - Moen, Espen R.
Y1  - 1997/04/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/262077
DO  - 10.1086/262077
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 385
EP  - 411
VL  - 105
IS  - 2
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - In this paper, I construct an equilibrium for markets with frictions, which is competitive in the sense that all agents are price takers and maximize utility subject to a set of market parameters. I show that the equilibrium allocation is socially optimal. I also show how the competitive search equilibrium can be achieved if employers with vacancies can advertise publicly the wages they pay.
AB  - In this paper, I construct an equilibrium for markets with frictions, which is competitive in the sense that all agents are price takers and maximize utility subject to a set of market parameters. I show that the equilibrium allocation is socially optimal. I also show how the competitive search equilibrium can be achieved if employers with vacancies can advertise publicly the wages they pay.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/262077
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/262077
Y2  - 2024/03/23
